They should be arriving at the
North Pole in a few hours.

51
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,958
Tsubaki, you should lie
down a little longer.

52
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:23,291
If I fall into a deep sleep
right now I'm positive

53
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:25,291
that I won't ever wake up again.

54
00:04:25,375 --> 00:04:28,291
Am I not right Chizuru?

55
00:04:28,375 --> 00:04:29,375
Yes.

56
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:31,041
But before that happens.

57
00:04:31,125 --> 00:04:33,291
I should return your
body to the Coagula.

58
00:04:33,375 --> 00:04:34,541
The Coagula.

59
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:36,416
We've detected
some abnormalities

60
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,125
in each of the island's blocs.

61
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:40,875
We've been unable to
stop the animals and plants

62
00:04:40,958 --> 00:04:43,250
on the island from dying,
one after another.

63
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:46,666
The island's MIR's doing it
because it learned about death.

64
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:49,583
What does she mean by that?
What's going on?

65
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:51,875
The MIR which controls
all the island's functions

66
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:54,750
can acquire an infinite
amount of information.

67
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:57,750
It has learned about the cycle
of life and it's now trying

68
00:04:57,833 --> 00:05:01,291
to die along with Tsubaki
since she is the island's core.

69
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:05,166
Before I can go, I must
teach the MIR one last thing.

70
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:08,041
It must now learn to understand
that the end of a life,

71
00:05:08,125 --> 00:05:10,666
gives rise to the
beginning of a new one.

72
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:13,333
Life and death are merely
extensions of each other

73
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:15,041
and they continue on as one.

74
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:16,375
But wait.

75
00:05:16,458 --> 00:05:19,291
The MIR is located
somewhere on this island, right?

76
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:21,791
And if that's what's
killing the island then...

77
00:05:21,875 --> 00:05:24,375
She's right. Why don't
we just get rid of it!

78
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:26,958
Then Tsubaki won't have
to suffer anymore.

79
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:28,500
It's not that simple.

80
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:29,916
The air that you
are now breathing...

81
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,833
...is the MIR.

82
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:33,333
We're breathing the MIR?

83
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,125
The air that is within our
mirrored camouflage system...

84
00:05:36,208 --> 00:05:38,416
...is basically
this island's MIR.

85
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:41,666
It exists living with us,
as a mass of gas that's

86
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:44,166
a part of the island,
and as it circulates,

87
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:47,000
it accumulates information.

88
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:48,500
It doesn't exist anywhere...

89
00:05:48,583 --> 00:05:51,125
...and at the same time
it exists everywhere.

90
00:05:51,208 --> 00:05:54,666
In other words, the MIR is this
island's environment itself.

91
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:56,333
The air?

92
00:05:56,416 --> 00:05:59,791
But I thought the MIR always
took the form of a crystal?

93
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:01,958
When it met Fumihiko
and the others,

94
00:06:02,041 --> 00:06:04,333
the island's MIR
began to change.

95
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:06,833
That's when it started
to become a life form.

96
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:08,000
Isn't that right?

97
00:06:08,083 --> 00:06:09,250
Yes.

98
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:11,625
The MIR once was indeed
a crystallized mineral.

99
00:06:11,708 --> 00:06:14,541
But then it suddenly
evolved into a biosphere and

100
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:17,125
changed itself into
the air that surrounded us.

101
00:06:17,208 --> 00:06:18,708
Biosphere?
What is that?

102
00:06:18,791 --> 00:06:21,041
It's an independent
environment that's capable

103
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:23,416
of supporting many life forms.

104
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:26,000
That was the first step
towards co-existence

105
00:06:26,083 --> 00:06:28,208
between Festum and humans.

106
00:06:28,291 --> 00:06:32,208
Eventually, when the MIR fully
understands the cycle of life,

107
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:35,250
then this island will
exist as Earth does.

108
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:37,333
It will be able to keep
us alive whether we're

109
00:06:37,416 --> 00:06:40,458
in space or at the
bottom of the ocean.

110
00:06:40,541 --> 00:06:43,416
The reason I am able to control
everything on this island

111
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:46,750
is because the MIR
is the island's air.

112
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:48,416
And so I must now return to the

113
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,583
island's Coagula for
this same reason.

114
00:06:51,666 --> 00:06:53,458
If I stay out here,

115
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:56,833
every being's life that
depends on this MIR...

116
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,583
...they will also die.

117
00:06:58,666 --> 00:07:00,250
It can't be.

118
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:02,625
The MIR is still in the
process of growing up.

119
00:07:02,708 --> 00:07:05,708
Little by little, it's learning
about life and death.

120
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:09,750
I can't stop the lesson before
I've finished teaching it.

121
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,041
But why you?

122
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:13,458
Why do you have to
sacrifice yourself, Tsubaki?

123
00:07:13,541 --> 00:07:16,541
The bittersweet story...
the happiness and the sadness...

124
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:20,416
...that can only come from
having truly been alive...

125
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,166
I wanted to
experience that,

126
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:26,000
and this was the only
for me to do it.

127
00:07:26,083 --> 00:07:27,916
The radar is picking
up a lot of activity.

128
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,666
Well, it's about time.
I'll lower our altitude.

129
00:07:33,291 --> 00:07:35,166
They're so many of them.

130
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:37,958
And the skies are
filled with just as many.

131
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:41,416
The Neo U.N. put together quite
an impressive military force.

132
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,791
What if they still end
up getting defeated?

133
00:07:43,875 --> 00:07:46,625
I guess it would mean the
end of the human race.

134
00:07:47,041 --> 00:07:48,666
For those parties
joining the battle,

135
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,625
transmit your
authorization code.

136
00:07:50,708 --> 00:07:53,875
This is Tatsumiya Island's
Fafner unit reporting.

137
00:07:53,958 --> 00:07:56,291
We decided to
join your little party.

138
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:57,958
So? You gonna
wish us luck?

139
00:07:58,041 --> 00:08:00,125
I trust you'll refrain
from attacking us.

140
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:01,875
We are on the
same side, after all.

141
00:08:01,958 --> 00:08:03,333
Yeah.
All right.

142
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,291
But the same goes
for you too, Barns.

143
00:08:05,375 --> 00:08:06,791
Which means no friendly fire.

144
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:09,750
We have no intention of wasting
any of our bullets on you.

145
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:12,833
That said, each unit
will be acting independently

146
00:08:12,916 --> 00:08:15,041
which means you're
responsible for your own safety.

147
00:08:15,125 --> 00:08:17,166
What? I don't quite follow you.

148
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:20,333
Because the enemy has mind
reading capabilities, it will be

149
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:23,250
far more effective if each
unit maneuvers on their own.

150
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:26,333
So we're not so much as fighting
with humans as among them.

151
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:27,875
Correct.

152
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:30,291
No one unit will be able to
anticipate another's actions.

153
00:08:30,375 --> 00:08:33,875
In essence it's full scale
guerrilla warfare.

154
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:38,666
You've been approved.
You are now the 127th unit.

155
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:41,666
I wish you guys luck.
May we all survive.

156
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,625
How could they just abandon the
chain of command like that?

157
00:08:44,708 --> 00:08:47,083
When you're launching an all
out war against the Festum,

158
00:08:47,166 --> 00:08:49,125
this is the most
effective strategy.

159
00:08:49,208 --> 00:08:52,000
Okay kiddos...
Did you hear the update?

160
00:08:52,083 --> 00:08:53,041
Yes.

161
00:08:53,125 --> 00:08:54,666
Don't worry.
It won't be a problem.

162
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:56,541
We can basically
do what we want, right?

163
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:59,375
I think it ends up being
more convenient for us.

164
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:01,375
We'll be arriving shortly.

165
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:04,000
Until then, I suggest you
go over your plan of attack.

166
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:07,541
Roger that. Kenji.
Will you do it?

167
00:09:07,916 --> 00:09:09,125
You want me to do it?

168
00:09:09,208 --> 00:09:11,083
You're student
council president.

169
00:09:11,666 --> 00:09:13,000
Oh. Right.

170
00:09:13,083 --> 00:09:15,458
Everyone take a
look at the monitor!

171
00:09:15,541 --> 00:09:18,166
We will arrive at point A
and then proceed to point B

172
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:20,000
with the first round of weapons.

173
00:09:20,083 --> 00:09:22,000
During that time
Mr. Mizoguchi'll prepare

174
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:24,625
weaponry reinforcements
and drop them at point B.

175
00:09:24,708 --> 00:09:27,125
From there we will
enter enemy territory,

176
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:28,708
and contact Kazuki's mom.

177
00:09:28,791 --> 00:09:30,458
I mean, the targeted core

178
00:09:30,541 --> 00:09:32,541
to get information on
Soshi's whereabouts.

179
00:09:32,625 --> 00:09:35,916
After we've rescued Soshi
we'll then head to point D.

180
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,833
Meanwhile
Mr. Mizoguchi and others

181
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:40,916
will transfer to a recovery
aircraft and wait for us there.

182
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,250
How was that?
All right?

183
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:44,416
You did great, Kenji.
Thanks.

184
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,041
Now, confirm our formations
would you Canon?

185
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:49,916
Why me? Aren't you
the squadron leader?

186
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,333
But you have more real world
fighting experience than I do.

187
00:09:54,083 --> 00:09:54,750
Understood.

188
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,083
Will ya look it that.

189
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:57,916
Kazuki knows
what he's doing.

190
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,500
Huh?
He does?

191
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:03,000
This style of battle is unlike
any of their previous ones.

192
00:10:03,083 --> 00:10:04,916
Everyone fighting
it is a commander,

193
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:08,250
yet at the same time
they are also just a soldier.

194
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:09,666
During the battles,

195
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,583
we will be using a four-in-one
cross dock formation.

196
00:10:12,666 --> 00:10:14,625
Kazuki's Mark Sein
will take the lead,

197
00:10:14,708 --> 00:10:17,125
while Kenji's Mark Acht
will be the right wing.

198
00:10:17,208 --> 00:10:18,916
My Mark Drei will
be the left wing,

199
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,958
and Maya's Mark Sieben
will cover us from behind.

200
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:24,250
This may appear to be a
defensive formation,

201
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:27,041
but it actually concentrates
all of our firepower in the

202
00:10:27,125 --> 00:10:30,291
front which is ideal when
making a forced entry.

203
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:32,541
Which means the strategy
calls for us to annihilate all

204
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:34,958
enemies in front of us, for
there is no looking back.

205
00:10:35,041 --> 00:10:37,000
Our priority is
to reach that target.

206
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:39,291
Is this all right
with you, Kazuki?

207
00:10:39,375 --> 00:10:41,083
Thank you, Canon.
Nice work.

208
00:10:41,166 --> 00:10:42,541
Maya...

209
00:10:42,625 --> 00:10:45,541
Before we begin will you
remind all of us once again

210
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:48,458
about the most important
aspect of this operation.

211
00:10:48,541 --> 00:10:51,541
We will be stuck, unable to
perform any functions

212
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,250
or communicate
with each other...

213
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:56,125
If we happen to lose
even a single person.

214
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:59,875
So the important thing is...
that all of us make it back...

215
00:10:59,958 --> 00:11:03,166
All five of us...
that's including Soshi...

216
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:05,875
...will return back
to the island!

217
00:11:08,083 --> 00:11:09,708
Looks like it's begun.

